==Points of interest==
Lancaster County is home to the historic church of St. Mary&#x27;s, Whitechapel, founded in 1669. Mary Ball Washington, mother of George Washington, was born in the parish of St. Mary&#x27;s. Rappahannock General Hospital is in Kilmarnock, it is the only hospital on the Northern Neck.
Other attractions are:
* Irvington Steamboat Museum
* Windmill Point Beach
* Belle Isle State Park
* Chilton Woods State Forest
* Ampro Shipyard
* Historic Christ Church

==See also==
* National Register of Historic Places listings in Lancaster County, Virginia

